04/04/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The Ashkalia community will be registered for the first time as an ethnicity in Kosovo during a two-week census which started on April 1st, media reported on Sunday (April 3rd). In the last census -- 30 years ago -- they were declared Albanians. It is estimated there are around 35,000 Ashkalia community members living in Kosovo, mostly in the Ferizaj region.(KLAN Kosova, RTK, Kohavision - 03/04/11)
